metadata.name: Milano-223
metadata.description:
Milano-223 represents for me one of the first approaches to the photogrammetry technique.
I grew up in a little town of just over 5,000 inhabitants. Starting to live Milan inspired me a lot: chaos, speed, buildings, subway, art.
I owe a lot to this city and I'm very happy to be able to show it what it has in part transmitted to me.
Grazie Milano.

Gabriele Verga (2023)
3584x2048
Piazza Sempione, 17-23 April, w/ ReasonedArt
